{"mode":"repetition","description":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Analyse the given cards carefully and try to guess the correct answers.<\/strong><\/p>\n","dialogs":[{"tips":{},"text":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>You can draw pictures and colour them. What is the name of the Software?<\/strong><\/p>\n","answer":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>MS Paint<\/strong><\/p>\n","imageAltText":"Logo","audio":[{"path":"audios\/audio-60e7ed51c2750.mp3","mime":"audio\/mpeg","copyright":{"license":"U"}}],"image":{"path":"images\/image-60e8358fb9d71.png","mime":"image\/png","copyright":{"license":"U"},"width":512,"height":512}},{"tips":{},"text":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>What are the parts of a paint screen? Name them.<\/strong><\/p>\n","answer":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>1.Title Bar<br>\n2.Colour Palette<br>\n3.Toolbox<br>\n4.Menu Bar<br>\n5.Drawing Area<\/strong><\/p>\n","imageAltText":"Paint overlay","audio":[{"path":"audios\/audio-60e7ed58b08ac.mp3","mime":"audio\/mpeg","copyright":{"license":"U"}}],"image":{"path":"images\/image-60e837f97af6a.png","mime":"image\/png","copyright":{"license":"U"},"width":898,"height":607}},{"tips":{},"text":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>What is a tool box in Paint?&nbsp;<\/strong><\/p>\n","answer":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Tool box is a part of paint screen. It contains different types of tools which helps us to draw.<\/strong><\/p>\n","imageAltText":"Tool box","audio":[{"path":"audios\/audio-60e7ed5f64242.mp3","mime":"audio\/mpeg","copyright":{"license":"U"}}],"image":{"path":"images\/image-60e838d0a3823.png","mime":"image\/png","copyright":{"license":"U"},"width":898,"height":607}},{"tips":{},"text":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>It is used for drawing free-hand pictures. Which tool is this?<\/strong><\/p>\n","answer":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Pencil Tool<\/strong><\/p>\n","imageAltText":"Pencil tool","audio":[{"path":"audi